data:
This project “EKOFILI”, which will take place in Kryoneri Korinthia (Greece), consists from three activities (1 training seminar and 2 flows of Group-EVS) involving 10 European programme countries (Greece, Italy, Slovakia, Austria, Spain, Turkey, Liechtenstein, Finland, Luxembourg and United Kingdom). The Training seminar will last 8 days (including travel), 8-15/5/2017, gathering in a balanced way (gender and countries) 22 participants (2 per country), 2 experts & staff.
The volunteering activities will take place during the period 1-30.6.2017 and 1-31.05.2018 involving the same partners, gathering in these 2 EVS-flows 24 young volunteers in total, the most of them with less opportunities.

Having in mind the urgency of a sustainable development in our societies, the idea behind this project is to empower youth workers and their organisations to support social and environmental responsibility, by saving and optimising resources. 

The training seminar “EKOFILI” intends to train youth workers to reuse recycled materials and provide them with competences, to act as multipliers in their own organisations / countries.

The training programme has the following objectives:
· the promotion of land tourism's sustainability;
· the reuse of recycled material for wooden constructions;
· the construction of a tree-house for environmental seminars;
- the development of an educational permaculture garden.

Target is:
- to stimulate the spirit of entrepreneurship for participants, by involving them in activities, where they will develop ideas and abilities to reuse recycled materials;
- to encourage creativity, leadership skills, innovative attitude and environmental responsibility of participants, to be able to act as multipliers of the knowledge acquired in the training course.

In the “EKOFILI” Group EVS-placements the volunteers will have the following tasks: 
- work on rural and sustainable development and environmental protection, connected with land tourism's development;
- maintain environmental footpaths, by reusing recycled material for wooden constructions;
- constructing a tree-house for seminar purposes;
- developing flora and fauna information panels; 
- setting up an educational permaculture garden;
- creating outdoor mosaics;
- reconstruct a traditional building;
- take part in agrotourism activities.

Through different activities offered to young volunteers and especially those with fewer opportunities, a serious chance to do something new, positive and special in their lives will be given to them. By participating in this project the volunteers will gain more self-confidence, will learn to be more independent, to take responsibility for themselves and the others. This new experience will give them strength, to search for new possibilities in their lives. 

All activities will have visible results and impact to the local community. The results are meant to be used by schools and education institutes and in this way, they will have longer term benefits.  
The goal of this project is to contribute as example to the sustainable rural development in Greece and Europe. 

Further the project aims to contribute for a sustainable identity within the Greek land tourism. Agrotourism is targeting the upgrading of quality, derived from local farming products and services & helps the development of local economy.
Its actions are supported by the Greek Agrotourism Federation-SEAGE (www.agroxenia.net) and local associations and entities.

The Youth Exchange “MOUNTAINS: what’s behind our fears” will promote integration of refugees, development cooperation and ICT among youngsters and local community. Mainly through outdoor/nature activities and forum theatre, the participants will raise awareness about these topics and be involved in several performances all over the region, in close interaction with local communities, also using ICT technologies as a tool. This project will be developed by 6 program countries – Portugal, Bulgaria, Italy, France, Greece and United Kingdom and will take place in Amarante (Portugal) during 9 days (travel days included), from 21st till 29th June 2017. It will gather in a balanced way (gender and countries) 24 participants (4 per country), aged between 18-25, and 6 youth leaders. It will also have an Advanced Planning Visit (APV) with all youth leaders from 27th till 30th May 2017 (travel days included) in Amarante. The main objectives are:
(1) Raise awareness about refugee and migrant’s issues; 
(2) Promote integration of refugees in small/medium scale cities involving local communities; 
(3) Promote forum theatre as a tool to develop social conscience and teach youngsters on how to change their world;
(4) Disseminate alternative approaches for economy such as Fair Trade and responsible consumption;
(5) Raise the spirit of cooperation among youngsters and between them and the community, fostering the values of solidarity and mutual understanding between people from different cultures, especially those under refugee and migrant’s statute.
Main activities and methods: during this Youth Exchange the participants will develop several activities using Non Formal Education (NFE) methodologies. The main activities will be centered on (1), document and test people’s behaviors regarding refugee and migrant’s (2) design a forum theatre performance to show around the region and (3) share the cultural diversity by organizing events such as gastronomy and intercultural nights. We will use different methods (workshops, outdoor activities, forum theatre, simulations, campaigning, street actions, intercultural night, show cooking, video and exhibitions, etc.) in order to assure that all participants can be involved and have an active role. We will assure a safe atmosphere of intercultural learning where participants can interact and cooperate with the common goal of participation and sharing their cultures and experiences.
Results and impact: we expect this Activity to create a new attitude among local community, especially young people, regarding refugees and migrants. We also expect that other stakeholders (public authorities, local social and cultural network, media, school board members, etc.) can focus on the topics of the Youth Exchange and reflect and understand the role in society that young people can have to using different NFE methodologies to integrate and support the refugees and migrants. The impact that this project seeks to create both in the participants and in the local community can be really significant, as the topic is nowadays crucial to understand and work on the future of Europe. Besides that it disseminates the opportunities for young people offered at EU level and applies alternative methods (NFE activities, forum theatre, visits, simulations, workshops, exhibitions, campaigning and outdoor activities) that allow a greater interaction within the group of participants and the community – sense of belonging. This approach is inclusive as it encourages other youngsters to be more participative and aware, thus transforming their way of thinking and perceiving reality, passing it to the community.

This European Voluntary Service project is developed at Centro Social de Palmela (CSP), in Palmela's council with international partners from the United Kingdom; Austria; Spain, Finland, Italy, Hungary, Estonia & local partners like the municipality and other local cultural, youth, social organizations & networks. 
It's the second edition of a short-term project, split into 2 main activities with 7 participants (fewer opportunities, gender balanced, 18-30 years old)for 55 and 57 days, between March 2018 and August 2018.

The main objective of this project is the empowerment and social inclusion of young people through educational non-formal activities, artistic and active participation activities, promoting diversity and understanding, personal, social and local development, citizenship, leading to a stronger European cohesion.

“Busy building” is in link with the European current concerns and realities, namely the objectives of sustainability, local development, respect for cultural diversity, active participation, entrepreneurship, employability and inclusion.

Busy Building project's topic - based on Art, Culture & Participation - developing a creative, participative, positive and dynamic approach, through non-formal education and inclusive activities, locally, with a European dimension and values.

CSP's mission is also to support and participate in this global action towards European goals. That's why we wish to develop this project in Palmela's council  (35 km from Lisbon). It's a council divided in rural (strong long-term unemployment and geographical, educational and cultural isolation) and urban.
The origin of the project is connected with the needs of our social centre and the needs of our local partners and community, urgently looking for better answers to their social, educational and inclusion needs.

It's a high-level challenging group project, at a local, regional and international level, developed with groups with fewer opportunities youngsters,  with strong and visible impacts towards direct participants, partner organisations and youth in general, including the ones living it the "Shelter House Porta Aberta" in Palmela (Youth House neighbours).

The project wishes to:
- give an international and inclusive character to the activities of the organization, "refreshing" projects of the organisation & local community;
- spread the European ideals/values and help to reach the EU goals;
-  support languages learning & development;
- promote the exchange of cultures, knowledge & traditions;
- create a real possibility to young volunteers of non-formal education in areas of their interests, contributing to their personal, social and professional development, promoting professional inclusion and entrepreneurship;
- educate for multiculturality, tolerance & team work;
- be an example for other youngsters, concerning mobility, volunteer work and active participation/citizenship in the frame of NFL.
- give real inclusive opportunities for young people with fewer opportunities;
- support the creation & development of a "Youth House" in Palmela ( dormitory, plenary room, Eurodesk point & eco-garden);
- support the creation & development of Youth Month celebration activities – Março a Partir – under the motto "Community – School of participation";
- refresh & support the renovation of CSP facilities & disadvantaged families houses (supported by the social projects).
Volunteers will work with a multidisciplinary team: animators, social workers, educators, helpers, youth workers, helpers from the general services (maintenance, cleaning, etc..), thinking, creating, planning, developing & evaluating activities.
It's a very wide & open project, so the tasks time-table will be also flexible according to the team, the profile, interests, ideas & needs.
The different volunteers activities associated with their ideas will be the main tool to create educational & participative ways of building healthy-learning- occupation. 
It's expected that the volunteers learning objectives are reached totally; at least to develop a new partnership with partners,  to motivate at least 20 youngsters for EVS; spread Erasmus + opportunities among 400 unemployed/social income users.
